	                <h3>Getting Started</h3>
	                <p>
	                    If you have planned to use the KNP Menu bundle or the KNP Pagination bundle, make sure you have declared them before the Foundation bundle in AppKernel.php.<br />
	                    Add the "florianbelhomme/foundation-bundle" in your Symfony2 project. For detailed installation instructions or issues, please visit <a href="https://github.com/florianbelhomme/FoundationBundle">the bundle on Github (https://github.com/florianbelhomme/FoundationBundle)</a><br />
	                    Your project is ready!
	                </p>
	            </div>
	        </div>
	
	        <div class="row" id="usage">
	            <div class="large-12 columns">
	                <h3>Common usage</h3>
	                <p>
	                    If you want to theme all your project with Foundation, the easiest way is to go into the app/config/config.yml and add at the end :<br />
	                    fb_foundation:<br />
                            theme: { form: true, knp_menu: true, knp_paginator: true }
	                </p>
	                <p>(But you can also theme specific elements, look into the bundle's readme for explainations)</p>
	            </div>
